00:01:32.560 --> 00:01:37.450
High Voltage is a project by Phillip David
Stearns that merges electronics with photography.

00:01:37.450 --> 00:01:43.049
He produces images by applying 15,000 volts
of electricity to instant color film, that's

00:01:43.049 --> 00:01:46.130
about 1,000 times the strength of a car battery.

00:01:46.130 --> 00:01:50.689
It creates an organic pattern and shows off
the ability of instant film beyond its typical

00:01:50.689 --> 00:01:53.250
use of capturing the world around us.

00:01:53.250 --> 00:01:58.600
Grand Pale Maw is a giant mural using only
latex paint and a black sharpie.

00:01:58.600 --> 00:02:02.899
It took artist Sean Sullivan seven months
to get to the point where he finally considered

00:02:02.899 --> 00:02:08.149
it done, partly because he exceeded his original
timeline by four months.

00:02:08.149 --> 00:02:18.819
Now for When the Lights Go Out 2, an art showcase
featuring glow in the dark prints.

00:02:18.819 --> 00:02:29.750
A'shop is a production company that creates
giant scale graffiti murals, street art, and

00:02:29.750 --> 00:02:30.750
urban aesthetics.

00:02:30.750 --> 00:02:35.150
They have a large collection of artists that
work for both commercial and private clients

00:02:35.150 --> 00:02:39.480
to make murals for interiors and exteriors
as well as custom art pieces.

